description:
An Electron app for uploading diabetes device data to Tidepool's backend

Tidepool Uploader is a universal uploader app that allows you to retrieve data from supported devices, including every brand of insulin pump and continuous glucose monitor (CGM) on the US market and a wide variety of blood glucose meters and diabetes apps.
What's Changed
- Allow VERSION_SHA to be specified directly (UPLOAD-1441) by @darinkrauss in #1675
- [UPLOAD-1440] dep updates by @krystophv in #1676
- [UPLOAD-1459] Add qa4 and qa5 to .config.js by @darinkrauss in #1680
- Add support for Embrace PRO meter (UPLOAD-1416) by @gniezen in #1679
- Remove JDRF logo in footer (UPLOAD-1460) by @gniezen in #1684
- Check if error submission was already clicked (UPLOAD-1462) by @gniezen in #1685
- Add support for Libre 2 CGMs used with Tandem pumps (UPLOAD-1228) by @gniezen in #1636
- Don't let power-only USB cable warning mask other errors (UPLOAD-1034) by @gniezen in #1681
- Improve device time modal descriptions (UPLOAD-1448) by @gniezen in #1683
- Fixes for Fora TN'G Voice meter (UPLOAD-1447) by @gniezen in #1678
Full Changelog: https://github.com/tidepool-org/uploader/compare/v2.61.0...v2.62.0
